•When it comes to art, it’s important not to hide the madness•

«I  would never chart a river or scale a peak to take its measure or plant a flag. There’s no point. It’s solipsistic self-aggrandizement. So too those scientist who study the planets seeking astronomical enlightenment for it’s own sake. The botanist studying the variegation of Amazonian fern. The zoologist caught up in the endless fascination of an adders coils. And for what? The elation of discovery? Knowledge for itself alone? Plant your flag on the truth? There is only one worthy goal for scientific exploration. Piercing the tissue that separates life from death. Everything else, from the deepest bottom of the sea to the top of the highest mountain of the farthest planet is insignificant.»

Son come falchi quei carri appostati,
corron parole sui visi arrossati, 
corre il dolore bruciando ogni strada 
e lancia grida ogni muro di Praga.
Dimmi chi era che il corpo portava, 
la città intera che lo accompagnava, 
la città intera che muta lanciava 
una speranza nel cielo di Praga,

“Il futuro che ti potevo dare l'ho
